review:
Decent light-hearted sim that provides all that you can expect. It is not a masterpiece but can easily scratch engineering itch and can be challenging if you try 100% it. Recommended for people who like casual puzzles.

Pros:
- Good optimisation;
- A lot of levels;
- Cartoony art style; 
- Intuitive controls;
- Good difficulty curve;

- Cons:
- Inconsistent physics;
- Mediocre soundtrack;

Unfortunately Steam only has "like" and "dislike" which makes it difficult, however;
AFL Evolution isn't a bad game, nor is it exactly good, there are a number of flaws, such as "easy" being way too easy and then "medium" being far too difficult, despite only being one difficulty step. The controls are well thought through, if a little difficult to learn.
6/10 - buy if you really like Footy, but possibly miss if you aren't big into it, just don't expect something with the polish of Fifa or Madden
